snippet: Steve Williams, who caddied for four notable golfers in his career and was inducted into the Caddie Hall of Fame last week, said he was ready to spend more time with his family in New Zealand.
abstract: Steve Williams, who caddied for four notable golfers in his career, including 13 years with Tiger Woods, is inducted into the Caddie Hall of Fame; says he is ready for more important things, like spending more time with his family in New Zealand.
lead_paragraph: Steve Williams, who caddied for four notable golfers in his career and was inducted into the Caddie Hall of Fame last week, said he was ready to spend more time with his family in New Zealand.

headline.main: After a Hall of Fame Induction, a Caddie Is Intent on Laying It Up
headline.print_headline: After a Hall of Fame Induction, a Caddie Is Intent on Laying It Up
